    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/corporate-body>;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Pažangiųjų tinklų ir paslaugų bendroji įmonė"@lt, "Fællesforetagendet for intelligente net og tjenester"@da, "Gemeinsames Unternehmen für intelligente Netze und Dienste"@de, "Älykkäät verkot ja palvelut ‑yhteisyritys"@fi, "Smart Networks and Services Joint Undertaking"@en, "Kopuzņēmums “Viedie tīkli un pakalpojumi”"@lv, "Impresa comune «Reti e servizi intelligenti»"@it, "Κοινή επιχείρηση «Έξυπνα δίκτυα και υπηρεσίες»"@el, "Společný podnik pro inteligentní sítě a služby"@cs, "Intelligens Hálózatok és Szolgáltatások Közös Vállalkozás"@hu, "Det gemensamma företaget för smarta nät och tjänster"@sv, "Skupno podjetje za pametna omrežja in storitve"@sl, "Întreprinderea comună „Rețele și servicii inteligente”"@ro, "Nutivõrkude ja -teenuste ühisettevõte"@et, "Wspólne Przedsięwzięcie na rzecz Inteligentnych Sieci i Usług"@pl, "L-Impriża Konġunta Networks u Servizzi Intelliġenti"@mt, "Gemeenschappelijke Onderneming “Slimme netwerken en diensten”"@nl, "Empresa Común para las Redes y los Servicios Inteligentes"@es, "Entreprise commune «Réseaux et services intelligents»"@fr, "Zajedničko poduzeće za pametne mreže i usluge"@hr, "Empresa Comum de Redes e Serviços Inteligentes"@pt, "An Comhghnóthas um Líonraí agus Seirbhísí Cliste"@ga, "Съвместно предприятие „Интелигентни мрежи и услуги“"@bg, "Spoločný podnik pre inteligentné siete a služby"@sk;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Smart Networks and Services Joint Undertaking is a public-private partnership which contributes to the general objectives of the Horizon Europe Regulation. Its general objectives are: to foster Europe’s technological sovereignty in future smart networks and services by reinforcing current industrial strengths and by extending the scope from 5G connectivity to the broader strategic value chain including cloud-based service provisioning as well as components and devices; to align strategic roadmaps of a wider range of industrial players; to advance European technological and scientific excellence to support European leadership to shape and master 6G systems by 2030; to strengthen the deployment of digital infrastructures and uptake of digital solutions in the European markets; to prepare the European smart networks and services supply industry; to facilitate digital innovation; to support the alignment of future smart networks and services with Union policy objectives."@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation> "SNSJU"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#LAC>, "COB0001653"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#XML_RECORD>, "SNSJU"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#NAC>, "SNSJU"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#WHOISWHO>, "SNSJU"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#PUB_CORP>;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "SNS JU"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#sameAs> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/corporate-body/SNSJU_2021_0>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/identifier> "SNSJU";
